We want people to witness.

17:49.624 --> 17:53.010
Yet, that's still pride.

17:53.470 --> 17:54.172
And guess what?

17:54.692 --> 17:57.597
Yet, that's still wrong.

17:58.338 --> 17:59.340
So how does this drive?

17:59.460 --> 18:08.374
And this is so hard for us to figure out how it all relates because it goes against what goes in our mind of what makes sense and what is right.

18:08.794 --> 18:10.076
But it doesn't for God.

18:10.156 --> 18:11.218
You see, for God,

18:11.426 --> 18:15.691
He tried his sin and he knows this really well because he knows of the original sin.

18:16.131 --> 18:20.496
The original sin of Lucifer, the angel Lucifer once upon a time.

18:20.816 --> 18:21.497
What was the sin?

18:21.857 --> 18:23.079
You guys remember this in the Bible?

18:23.459 --> 18:27.904
It was a thing that started him on the path to becoming Satan, the devil, the enemy.

18:29.606 --> 18:30.567
It was pride.

18:31.408 --> 18:33.630
Look how beautiful I am, he said, right?

18:34.511 --> 18:35.452
I'm so great.

18:36.213 --> 18:38.155
Why can't I be like God?

18:39.016 --> 18:40.498
His pride.

18:40.578 --> 18:42.099
led to his downfall.

18:42.860 --> 18:53.951
So while it doesn't seem like, oh, it's this horrible thing, like, oh, you know, what's wrong with being happy that I got a 4.0 or promotion or I'm so good at sports or good at whatever?

18:54.952 --> 18:56.193
God knows more than us.

18:56.273 --> 18:56.853
He's smart.

18:57.114 --> 18:58.975
He knows that even doesn't seem bad.

18:59.356 --> 19:00.897
It can lead to really bad things.

19:01.238 --> 19:03.500
He's seen it firsthand through Satan.

19:03.840 --> 19:06.483
That's why he gave us this verse in Proverbs, right?

19:06.983 --> 19:10.066
Pride goeth before destruction.

19:10.402 --> 19:12.885
and a hotty spirit before the fall.

19:13.266 --> 19:16.891
Pride is the prelude to bad things coming, right?

19:17.011 --> 19:22.839
Even though it doesn't seem like it's a horrible thing to be prideful and be proud of the things that you do.

19:23.319 --> 19:26.584
It could be the prelude to bad stuff.

19:26.744 --> 19:28.506
Here's the problems with pride.

19:28.947 --> 19:30.309
The problems with pride.

19:31.210 --> 19:35.235
Number one, pride ruins unity.

19:36.017 --> 19:37.138
Unity, right?

19:37.314 --> 19:40.399
We as Christians know this, we are the body of Christ.

19:40.799 --> 19:45.586
We're supposed to be working together as one, common goal, common effort.

19:45.626 --> 19:48.190
You can imagine like a football team, right?

19:48.230 --> 19:49.672
We did the Tampa football team for it.

19:49.692 --> 19:54.299
They're supposed to work together as one to win the game, right?

19:54.900 --> 19:57.103
What happens when one guy is too prideful?

19:57.123 --> 19:58.405
Like I said, you're just quarterback.

19:58.605 --> 19:59.607
You won the Super Bowl.

19:59.627 --> 20:00.388
You're the MVP.

20:00.769 --> 20:04.434
Those guys who get really prideful and push themselves up.

20:05.058 --> 20:05.699
That happens.

20:05.779 --> 20:06.680
That does happen sometimes.

20:06.760 --> 20:08.281
But what's wrong with that?

20:08.301 --> 20:10.543
And what do people say about those people that take that attitude?

20:10.563 --> 20:12.645
They say, hey, Mr. quarterback, you forgot.

20:12.706 --> 20:13.687
This is a team game.

20:14.227 --> 20:18.832
Even though you might have the best throw, you need a receiver who can catch the ball.

20:19.212 --> 20:24.297
Even though you have the best throw, you need an offensive line to protect you so you don't get hit.

20:24.777 --> 20:25.979
You need a whole team.

20:25.999 --> 20:28.621
You need a defense to stop the other side so that you can win.

20:29.082 --> 20:33.426
If you aren't all working together, your team's a loser.

20:33.794 --> 20:36.082
So you can't just say, it was all me.

20:36.364 --> 20:37.789
I'm the MVP quarterback.

20:37.929 --> 20:38.793
I did everything.

20:38.853 --> 20:40.499
It doesn't work that way.

20:41.523 --> 20:44.594
It shouldn't work that way in our lives either, right?

20:45.090 --> 20:47.653
whether it be your work or your family or anywhere else, right?

20:47.974 --> 20:49.415
To say that it's all about me.

20:49.776 --> 20:51.518
I'm the greatest guy, right?

20:51.778 --> 20:54.722
You guys are all beneath me and I did it all.

20:55.062 --> 20:57.966
No, you wanted to have a team effort working together.

20:58.086 --> 21:00.028
It doesn't work at work when you do it like that.

21:00.069 --> 21:01.891
You guys work with other people on teams and stuff.

21:02.291 --> 21:05.475
We know that doesn't work when one guy takes that kind of attitude.

21:05.535 --> 21:07.638
It turns off the whole rest of the team, right?

21:08.439 --> 21:10.962
And it doesn't even work

21:11.074 --> 21:12.576
in the spiritual context.

21:12.616 --> 21:14.058
We're all here supposed to be Christians, right?

21:14.378 --> 21:16.661
We're supposed to be working together for God.

21:16.681 --> 21:20.125
It's not supposed to be one person is better than the other, right?

21:20.466 --> 21:23.509
It's supposed to be, hey, are we all striving together?

21:23.930 --> 21:25.412
Hey, more people need to get safe.

21:25.472 --> 21:26.393
Are we working together?

21:26.693 --> 21:31.239
It doesn't matter that, hey, that guy, he witnessed the 10 people, like we gave the example before, right?

21:31.579 --> 21:32.120
It doesn't matter.

21:32.360 --> 21:33.321
He's got to keep working.

21:33.762 --> 21:34.703
You got to keep working.

21:34.883 --> 21:36.345
Everyone's got to keep working, right?

21:36.685 --> 21:37.987
It's not like, oh, you got 10.

21:38.267 --> 21:40.370
We're going to give you a parade or something.

21:40.994 --> 21:42.916
That just means that we didn't do even more.

21:42.936 --> 21:44.558
10, Mr. 10.

21:44.858 --> 21:45.679
Why don't you do 20?

21:45.879 --> 21:46.700
Why don't you do 30?

21:47.101 --> 21:47.361
Right?

21:47.461 --> 21:48.202
We're working together.

21:48.222 --> 21:50.404
Let's do more and more and more together.

21:50.825 --> 21:57.372
We want to be unified in Christ working more and not thinking about how great I am for what I did.

21:58.293 --> 22:02.257
And related to that, pride encourages comparison.

22:02.717 --> 22:02.898
Right?

22:03.779 --> 22:05.520
Oh, I did this.

22:05.841 --> 22:06.321
I'm better.

22:06.381 --> 22:07.643
You're worse.

22:08.023 --> 22:08.784
You're no good.

22:09.325 --> 22:10.706
And that leads to division.

22:10.818 --> 22:11.299
Doesn't it?

22:11.799 --> 22:12.680
It leads to division.

22:12.840 --> 22:16.024
Same thing like we said about the sports team, right?

22:16.324 --> 22:20.288
Where if the quarterback keeps saying, I'm the best, well, everyone else hates him now, right?

22:20.348 --> 22:23.772
Now he comes a bad leader, because he just keeps saying, I'm the best, right?

22:24.413 --> 22:25.934
Same thing in the congregation.

22:26.315 --> 22:30.880
Imagine that hypothetical guy I talked about, the one that said, I witnessed the 10 people in one day.

22:31.240 --> 22:33.142
And he starts saying, I'm the best.

22:33.503 --> 22:37.027
You guys are all losers, because you guys got zero people saved.

22:37.968 --> 22:40.210
How does that make everyone feel in the congregation?

22:40.482 --> 22:43.867
Do they feel like, oh, I'm going to serve God more now.

22:43.907 --> 22:45.049
I don't even feel terrible.

22:45.470 --> 22:48.554
This guy's jumping up and down and trying to measure himself.

22:49.616 --> 22:52.340
And this gets worse and worse, the more and more people do it.

22:52.601 --> 22:53.943
The more pride spreads.

22:53.983 --> 22:58.309
Because now it's not just the guy that says, oh, I got 10 people safe and I'm better than you.

22:58.630 --> 22:59.892
Now everyone's trying to measure.

23:00.453 --> 23:01.855
Oh, well, he got 10.

23:02.456 --> 23:03.157
I got one.

23:03.718 --> 23:04.799
Oh, this guy got two.

23:04.900 --> 23:05.701
He's no good.

23:05.741 --> 23:07.644
This guy got five.

23:08.305 --> 23:09.106
Where does it end?

23:09.346 --> 23:11.429
We know that doesn't work in the real world, right?

23:11.929 --> 23:16.675
Imagine at your school, right?

23:16.735 --> 23:21.821
If people are all always worried about, oh, this guy, who can get the highest grade?

23:21.841 --> 23:26.948
This is why some schools, they have the whole rating on a curve, you remember, right?

23:27.268 --> 23:28.970
Where everyone has to compete against each other.

23:28.990 --> 23:30.792
There can only be one A student, right?

23:31.133 --> 23:35.378
And everyone has to fight, and it leads to everyone being upset, right?

23:35.554 --> 24:05.170
and worried about it, and some people being prideful that, oh, I'm on the top end of the curve, and you're on the bottom end, and you know, I can get that A, and you gotta get the C, and this and that, we know it from real life, and we know how it applies, that the more we compare the less you do we have, the more we compare the less you do we have, and the more we compare, the less you do we have, the more extensivity we have, right?

24:05.378 --> 24:07.723
It furthers separation.

24:08.264 --> 24:11.972
The idea being that, oh, you start thinking, oh, I'm this great guy.

24:12.393 --> 24:15.099
Well, I only hang out with other great guys, right?

24:15.580 --> 24:16.301
It's like in school.

24:16.321 --> 24:17.644
Say, I'm the 4.0 student.

24:17.744 --> 24:19.929
I'm only hanging out with the 4.0 students now, right?

24:19.969 --> 24:23.396
I want to do the other people that are at my level, right?

24:23.937 --> 24:26.162
Yeah, I knew this guy back in,

24:26.274 --> 24:27.496
back in the school days, right?

24:27.556 --> 24:30.341
And we were talking once upon a time about dating and stuff, right?

24:30.361 --> 24:34.047
And we were talking about, oh, would you ever date, you know, we went to Cal Berkeley, right?

24:34.127 --> 24:38.855
So would you ever date someone that was like, just like a high school graduate that didn't go to college?

24:39.416 --> 24:42.781
And he was like, no, I would never even consider it.

24:42.861 --> 24:47.549
Dating someone that did not graduate from college, you know, I'm a juicy Berkeley graduate, right?

24:47.870 --> 24:50.514
Those people would be beneath me, so to speak, right?

24:50.850 --> 24:53.995
And I thought that was very narrow-minded to say, like, how do you know?

24:54.055 --> 24:57.220
How do you know you wouldn't meet someone that's high school, graduate, right?

24:57.340 --> 25:00.485
That only and didn't go to college and maybe that's the perfect person for you.

25:00.525 --> 25:00.885
How do you know?

25:01.246 --> 25:04.491
But that's the kind of attitude that, oh, I'm on this level.

25:05.092 --> 25:07.215
I need to be with other people on this level.

25:07.756 --> 25:10.860
And sadly, folks, that happens in the church too.

25:11.341 --> 25:15.628
Some people get the attitude of like, oh, I am a quote good Christian.

25:15.908 --> 25:17.350
So I only hang out with these people.

25:17.731 --> 25:19.794
These other people, I don't want to deal with them.

25:19.970 --> 25:21.933
Those guys are the losers, right?

25:22.373 --> 25:23.615
Oh, we don't care about them.

25:24.276 --> 25:29.423
Folks, that's completely antithetical to everything that Jesus taught, isn't it?

25:30.024 --> 25:33.309
Jesus was known for hanging out with the losers, wasn't he?

25:33.629 --> 25:38.115
He's won the hung out with the lame people, the disabled guys, right?

25:38.416 --> 25:41.460
The ones that nobody liked, like the tax collectors.

25:42.361 --> 25:48.690
Our job, if we think that we are so, quote, good, unquote, is to meet with everybody else,

25:48.834 --> 25:51.198
and lift everyone else up too, right?

25:51.458 --> 25:54.863
To make them, to encourage them, to make them better.

25:55.464 --> 25:59.771
We're not supposed to be separated, we're supposed to be unified, unified.

26:00.572 --> 26:06.501
You know, the more we follow pride, the more we follow the sin, look what happened to Edom, right?

26:07.002 --> 26:12.730
Edom was so prideful about them so great that they would laugh and mock at Israel.

26:13.171 --> 26:15.154
Oh, they're getting taken over, ha ha.

26:15.234 --> 26:17.277
I'm going to even join in on them getting taken over.

26:17.497 --> 26:18.979
That's how prideful they were.

26:19.419 --> 26:21.962
And folks, that's the same thing that we get locked into.

26:22.283 --> 26:24.526
That we want to make ourselves feel so good.

26:25.086 --> 26:26.007
Oh, I'm the best.

26:26.248 --> 26:27.289
I'm the greatest at this.

26:27.670 --> 26:31.034
I need to put down other people to make myself feel better.

26:31.414 --> 26:32.415
That's sin, folks.

26:32.836 --> 26:34.618
That's our pride leading in the sin.

26:35.179 --> 26:36.561
How bad is that?

26:36.901 --> 26:44.050
And of course, the biggest danger of pride, the biggest danger of pride, is that it leads us to reject God.

26:44.386 --> 26:46.630
When our attitude becomes, I am so great.

26:47.452 --> 26:48.634
I'm the 4.0 student.

26:48.854 --> 26:49.255
I did it.

26:49.275 --> 26:51.319
I'm the quarterback that won the Super Bowl.

26:51.559 --> 26:51.900
I did it.

26:52.080 --> 26:53.142
I'm MVP, right?

26:53.963 --> 26:55.606
I am the greatest soul winner.

26:56.027 --> 26:58.271
I got 50 people saved ever.

26:58.632 --> 27:00.716
When that word, I becomes the number one thing.

27:01.257 --> 27:02.058
You've got it wrong.

27:02.138 --> 27:03.160
You've rejected God.

27:03.701 --> 27:06.807
Because the answer is supposed to be, God is great.

27:07.588 --> 27:08.690
I accomplished this.

27:08.802 --> 27:10.665
Thanks be to God, praise be to God.

27:11.025 --> 27:15.432
A lot of people, I got the 4.0, thanks be to God that he helped me get it.

27:15.913 --> 27:20.539
I got the raise at work, thanks be to God, because God could take it away from me in a second, right?

27:21.240 --> 27:24.726
Oh, 50 people got saved, it wasn't just me, it was God, right?

27:25.066 --> 27:26.989
God gave me the words, God helped me.

27:27.510 --> 27:29.132
We have to have that attitude.

27:29.653 --> 27:38.546
Once we lose that attitude, the more it becomes about me, me, me, the less we think about God, the less we care about God, the wrong path, that's what we get on.

27:38.946 --> 27:44.473
I'm not surprised that Eden was destroyed for their pride because they turned away from God.

27:44.873 --> 27:45.975
They turned away from God.

27:46.015 --> 27:48.638
They probably were too prideful and said in the Bible here.

27:49.018 --> 27:51.842
They probably thought too much of themselves.

27:51.862 --> 27:53.003
What does God wants us to be?

27:53.324 --> 27:57.088
God wants us to be humble, humble, right?

27:57.449 --> 27:59.211
We're supposed to be Christ-like, right?

27:59.351 --> 28:08.082
And who was more humbled in Christ, born in a manger, living his life as a regular guy, a carpenter, a no-name,

28:08.418 --> 28:08.739
Right?

28:09.239 --> 28:17.973
Even during his ministry, simply going around, not like a king with gold and jewels, but as a regular man of the people.

28:18.374 --> 28:19.376
We ought to be Christ's life.

28:19.596 --> 28:20.498
And what did he teach?

28:20.858 --> 28:21.539
What did he teach?

28:22.120 --> 28:27.188
He taught this, Matthew 2027, and whosoever shall be chief among you, let him what?

28:27.589 --> 28:30.754
Not let him get a parade and be honored and be arrogant.

28:31.696 --> 28:33.138
Let him be your servant.

28:33.506 --> 28:38.256
His challenge for us is not who can be the most prideful, who can be the most accomplished.

28:38.276 --> 28:46.873
It's who can be the best servant, who can be the most humble, the first shall be last and the last shall be first.

28:48.697 --> 28:49.819
That's his challenge to us.

28:50.561 --> 28:55.250
The best person, the number one guy, the guy that God loves the most,

28:55.810 --> 28:58.336
is the guy that serves the other person the most.

28:58.657 --> 29:00.521
Not the guy that says, I did it all.

29:00.641 --> 29:01.363
I'm number one.

29:01.523 --> 29:02.425
I'm the greatest guy.

29:02.546 --> 29:03.087
I'm whoever.

29:03.448 --> 29:06.294
Look at Paul for all the things he did.

29:06.314 --> 29:08.640
You would say he was the greatest missionary.

29:09.121 --> 29:10.584
Each one of his epistles, what does he say?

29:11.246 --> 29:14.834
Glory to God by the grace of God.

29:15.394 --> 29:16.355
Is that our attitude?

29:16.655 --> 29:19.918
That all our accomplishments are just by the grace of God.

29:20.199 --> 29:27.145
Not by anything I did, not by my own special talents, not by my own way, but through God.

29:28.086 --> 29:29.587
Let's wrap it up with the conclusion here.

29:30.068 --> 29:33.151
The quote here says, Sin came through the pride of Lucifer.

29:33.731 --> 29:36.774
You know, if we have pride, we're following Lucifer's path.

29:37.175 --> 29:38.776
But what did salvation come from?

29:39.397 --> 29:42.199
Salvation came through the humility of Jesus.

29:42.800 --> 29:44.882
We're gonna be like Jesus, humble.

29:45.090 --> 29:47.333
and not like Lucifer prideful.

29:47.874 --> 29:48.835
Let's pray.

29:48.855 --> 29:50.517
Dear God, thank you for your word, the Bible.

29:50.898 --> 29:55.824
This book of Obadiah, we rarely study it, but has a good message for us about pride.

29:56.185 --> 30:04.616
A tough message, one that maybe you don't want to hear, because sometimes we do want to be proud of our accomplishments, but Lord, keep us in check.

30:04.636 --> 30:11.005
Keep us from saying that we are so great, but remember that always that God is so great.

30:11.566 --> 30:14.770
And pray all these things in Jesus' name, amen.

